pretty complex problems will be revealed :)\r\n\r\nCome and learn how to replace your compaines ESB and make everyone happier in the process !','<p>Node.Js + 0MQ = Enterprise power </p>\n\n<p>We will be talking through how ZeroMQ and node.js play together very nicely and the awesomely neat code for some pretty complex problems will be revealed :)</p>\n\n<p>Come and learn how to replace your compaines ESB and make everyone happier in the process !</p>','0000-00-00','18:30:00','00:00:00','Gauteng','Johannesburg','','44 Stanley Ave, Johannesburg, 2092, South Africa','-26.18547','28.019019999999955','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=44+Stanley+Ave,+Johannesburg,+2092,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1e950c0a7a180075:0xabc336394e358c99','http://www.meetup.com/Jozi-Node-JS/events/177246052',72,'2014-11-11 14:56:04',1,'2015-10-21 22:27:50'),(16,1,'Rise of Microservices','rise-of-microservices','info@nodeza.co.za','','Microservices are a very old idea that has picked up a new head of steam, and are becoming a very popular approach to building a','Microservices are a very old idea that has picked up a new head of steam, and are becoming a very popular approach to building applications with node.js.\r\n\r\nInstead of building a single application, why not build many applications that communicate over standard network protocols? With each service being very small (often around 100 lines of code), they become very easy to build and compose into new systems.\r\n\r\nWhile they do have a lot of promise of being much more developer friendly, flexible and scaleable, there is no such thing as a silver bullet, and every benefit comes with some drawbacks.\r\n\r\nAdrian Rossouw, CTO of Wayfinder will share his experiences from migrating a monolythic application onto a new microservice architecture, including vexing questions such as how to deploy and manage your services,  configuration management and just how this all applies to the front-end.','<p>Microservices are a very old idea that has picked up a new head of steam, and are becoming a very popular approach to building applications with node.js.</p>\n<p>Instead of building a single application, why not build many applications that communicate over standard network protocols? With each service being very small (often around 100 lines of code), they become very easy to build and compose into new systems.</p>\n<p>While they do have a lot of promise of being much more developer friendly, flexible and scaleable, there is no such thing as a silver bullet, and every benefit comes with some drawbacks.</p>\n<p>Adrian Rossouw, CTO of Wayfinder will share his experiences from migrating a monolythic application onto a new microservice architecture, including vexing questions such as how to deploy and manage your services,  configuration management and just how this all applies to the front-end.</p>\n','2014-12-04','18:30:00','09:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','Woodstock, Cape Town, South Africa','-33.930556','18.44722200000001','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=Woodstock,+Cape+Town,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc5da25b1b83cb:0x9528ebc70c50cb86','http://www.meetup.com/nodecpt/events/199313432',54,'2015-02-13 06:35:09',0,'2015-10-25 10:13:22'),(17,1,'12 Factor services in NodeJS','12-factor-services-in-nodejs','info@nodeza.co.za','','Following our discussion of Microservices, next up we will delve into each principle of http://12factor.net/ to build scaleable ','Following our discussion of Microservices, next up we will delve into each principle of http://12factor.net/ to build scaleable and manageable systems in the context of NodeJS. More details to follow.','<p>Following our discussion of Microservices, next up we will delve into each principle of http://12factor.net/ to build scaleable and manageable systems in the context of NodeJS. More details to follow.</p>\n','2015-01-28','18:30:00','21:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','6 Beach Rd, Mouille Point, Cape Town, 8005, South Africa','-33.9020307','18.39956649999999','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=6+Beach+Rd,+Mouille+Point,+Cape+Town,+8005,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc67343dd19199:0x6b82684ba013bcfc','http://www.meetup.com/nodecpt/events/219127910',76,'2015-02-13 06:37:19',0,'2015-10-20 10:04:23'),(18,1,'Node, microservices and IOLmobile','node-microservices-and-iolmobile','info@nodeza.co.za','','The talk kicks off with general intro to NodeJS and its cost/benefit, similarly with microservices. I will present how we applie','The talk kicks off with general intro to NodeJS and its cost/benefit, similarly with microservices. I will present how we applied Node microservices to some use-cases, namely for weather, search, and matric results, for the IOLmobile.co.za AngularJS app.\r\n\r\n\"Weather\" (http://iolmobile.co.za/#!/weath...­) illustrates parsing and transforming XML data to be served as JSON, for consumption by the front-end AngularJS app. \"Matric results\" (http://iolmobile.co.za/#!/matri...­) illustrates using Redis as a fast in-memory database. \"Search\" (http://iolmobile.co.za/#!/searc...­) illustrates integration with ElasticSearch.','<p>The talk kicks off with general intro to NodeJS and its cost/benefit, similarly with microservices. I will present how we applied Node microservices to some use-cases, namely for weather, search, and matric results, for the IOLmobile.co.za AngularJS app.</p>\n<p>&quot;Weather&quot; (http://iolmobile.co.za/#!/weath...­) illustrates parsing and transforming XML data to be served as JSON, for consumption by the front-end AngularJS app. &quot;Matric results&quot; (http://iolmobile.co.za/#!/matri...­) illustrates using Redis as a fast in-memory database. &quot;Search&quot; (http://iolmobile.co.za/#!/searc...­) illustrates integration with ElasticSearch.</p>\n','2015-02-24','18:30:00','21:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','6 Beach Rd, Mouille Point, Cape Town, 8005, South Africa','-33.9020307','18.39956649999999','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=6+Beach+Rd,+Mouille+Point,+Cape+Town,+8005,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc67343dd19199:0x6b82684ba013bcfc','http://www.meetup.com/nodecpt/events/219127989',109,'2015-02-13 06:39:04',0,'2015-10-20 10:04:49'),(19,1,'Open hackday','open-hackday','info@nodeza.co.za','','Join us for a maker workshop day at Issi. We\'ll have a few talks and demos on 3D printing and related fields, but mainly the aim','Join us for a maker workshop day at Issi. We\'ll have a few talks and demos on 3D printing and related fields, but mainly the aim of the event is to get together and work on whatever projects we are busy with (provided that they can be done in a coffee shop environment) - for example we\'ll be working on a RepRap Prusa build. If you\'re going to be cutting or doing anything that could damage the surface, bring a cutting mat or a piece of masonite or similar.\r\n\r\nThe coffee shop will be open to order coffee and food.\r\n\r\nAnyone interested in the Maker movement, 3D printing, electronics, robotics, etc is welcome - no prior experience is necessary.','<p>Join us for a maker workshop day at Issi. We\'ll have a few talks and demos on 3D printing and related fields, but mainly the aim of the event is to get together and work on whatever projects we are busy with (provided that they can be done in a coffee shop environment) - for example we\'ll be working on a RepRap Prusa build. If you\'re going to be cutting or doing anything that could damage the surface, bring a cutting mat or a piece of masonite or similar.</p>\n<p>The coffee shop will be open to order coffee and food.</p>\n<p>Anyone interested in the Maker movement, 3D printing, electronics, robotics, etc is welcome - no prior experience is necessary.</p>\n','2014-12-14','10:00:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','140 Bree St, Cape Town City Centre, Cape Town, 8000, South Africa','-33.9232564','18.415738199999964','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=140+Bree+St,+Cape+Town+City+Centre,+Cape+Town,+8000,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc6765f514fb5f:0xe7a3270905a6a622','http://www.meetup.com/Cape-Town-Nodebots/events/219081235',69,'2015-02-13 06:42:59',0,'2015-10-20 10:02:49'),(20,1,'Nodebot brains: robots thinking in Javascript','nodebot-brains-robots-thinking-in-javascript','info@nodeza.co.za','','There are various microcontrollers that can be taught tricks using Javascript, some using wires some not.','Let\'s compare a Tessel (http://tessel.io ) with a pinocc.io (https://pinocc.io/) and have some raspi too. We will see how they speak Node to make a robot think or potentially make you toast.','<p>Let\'s compare a Tessel (http://tessel.io ) with a pinocc.io (https://pinocc.io/) and have some raspi too. We will see how they speak Node to make a robot think or potentially make you toast.</p>\n','2015-01-15','18:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','6 Beach Rd, Mouille Point, Cape Town, 8005, South Africa','-33.9020307','18.39956649999999','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=6+Beach+Rd,+Mouille+Point,+Cape+Town,+8005,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc67343dd19199:0x6b82684ba013bcfc','http://www.meetup.com/Cape-Town-Nodebots/events/219018118',64,'2015-02-13 06:44:46',0,'2015-10-20 10:05:24'),(21,1,'Checking out famous-views','topic-to-be-decided','info@nodeza.co.za','','This month we have Gadi Cohen as a speaker who will be running us through his famous-views package.','This month we have Gadi Cohen as a speaker who will be running us through his famous-views package.\r\n\r\nWe will also make time to help newcomers and answer questions. If there aren\'t too many questions we may have a look at the Velocity framework as well, as there have been questions in the past about end to end testing in Meteor.\r\n\r\nI apologise for the late notice. Future events will be scheduled a month in advance.\r\n\r\nIf there is load shedding the power will be cut at 8pm, hence the early end time. If there is no load shedding we will stick around a little longer to chat and ask or answer questions.','<p>This month we have Gadi Cohen as a speaker who will be running us through his famous-views package.</p>\n<p>We will also make time to help newcomers and answer questions. If there aren\'t too many questions we may have a look at the Velocity framework as well, as there have been questions in the past about end to end testing in Meteor.</p>\n<p>I apologise for the late notice. Future events will be scheduled a month in advance.</p>\n<p>If there is load shedding the power will be cut at 8pm, hence the early end time. If there is no load shedding we will stick around a little longer to chat and ask or answer questions.</p>\n','2015-02-18','18:00:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','3 Ravenscraig Rd, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.9296553','18.443542699999966','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=3+Ravenscraig+Rd,+Woodstock,+Cape+Town,+7915,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc5d9c697d1ffd:0xc5007595d81ab65','http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-Cape-Town/events/220408071',81,'2015-02-13 06:47:56',1,'2015-10-21 01:50:45'),(22,1,'Worldwide Meteor Day – Johannesburg','worldwide-meteor-day-johannesburg','info@nodeza.co.za','','Worldwide Meteor Day is when developers and folks interested in Meteor all over the world come together across the globe','Worldwide Meteor Day is when developers and folks interested in Meteor all over the world come together across the globe to:\r\n\r\n• see what amazing projects have been built with Meteor\r\n\r\n• meet awesome local Meteorites\r\n\r\n• bring a friend to the movement\r\n\r\n• get their questions answered by Meteor core developers and Meteor experts\r\n\r\n• connect with other cities\r\n\r\nAgenda of the Meteor Day:\r\n\r\n6pm: Introduction to Meteor and showcase of new Tutorial and example apps\r\n\r\n6:30pm: Everyone pulls out laptops to install and deploy an app (think of questions you\'ll want to ask in the Q&A)\r\n\r\n6:59pm: Take a group photo, tweet it :)\r\n\r\n7pm: Q&A Live stream with core devs or local experts\r\n\r\n7:30pm: Local Show&Tell lightning Talk Sessions\r\n\r\n~8pm: Social/Hacking time\r\n\r\nThis is a good chance to demo your project, promote your startup and find like minded individuals.\r\n\r\nIf there\'s enough of us, we can stage a mini-hackathon and demo the results after.\r\n\r\nhttp://meteorday.com','<p>Worldwide Meteor Day is when developers and folks interested in Meteor all over the world come together across the globe to:</p>\n<p>• see what amazing projects have been built with Meteor</p>\n<p>• meet awesome local Meteorites</p>\n<p>• bring a friend to the movement</p>\n<p>• get their questions answered by Meteor core developers and Meteor experts</p>\n<p>• connect with other cities</p>\n<p>Agenda of the Meteor Day:</p>\n<p>6pm: Introduction to Meteor and showcase of new Tutorial and example apps</p>\n<p>6:30pm: Everyone pulls out laptops to install and deploy an app (think of questions you\'ll want to ask in the Q&amp;A)</p>\n<p>6:59pm: Take a group photo, tweet it :)</p>\n<p>7pm: Q&amp;A Live stream with core devs or local experts</p>\n<p>7:30pm: Local Show&amp;Tell lightning Talk Sessions</p>\n<p>~8pm: Social/Hacking time</p>\n<p>This is a good chance to demo your project, promote your startup and find like minded individuals.</p>\n<p>If there\'s enough of us, we can stage a mini-hackathon and demo the results after.</p>\n<p>http://meteorday.com</p>\n','2014-11-06','18:00:00','00:00:00','Gauteng','Johannesburg','','Johannesburg, South Africa','-26.2041028','28.047305100000017','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=Johannesburg,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1e950c68f0406a51:0x238ac9d9b1d34041','http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-Johannesburg/events/211202182',44,'2015-02-13 06:58:08',0,'2015-10-20 10:04:54'),(23,1,'Worldwide Meteor Day – Cape Town','worldwide-meteor-day-cape-town','info@nodeza.co.za','','Come join Meteor Cape Town for Worldwide Meteor Day (meteorday.com)! The whole Meteor community is holding simultaneous meetups ','Come join Meteor Cape Town for Worldwide Meteor Day (meteorday.com)! The whole Meteor community is holding simultaneous meetups around the world on Nov 6, open to anyone who is interested in learning more about the Meteor platform. You’ll get to meet developers who have built things with Meteor here in Cape Town, play with the new Meteor examples and tutorial, and have Q&A via Hangout with a core developer or expert from the community. We’ll have free Meteor t-shirts and stickers in the new design as well. Be sure to bring your laptops for the deploy fest and open coworking.\r\n\r\nIf you’ve built a Meteor app before, we would love to see it during the show & tell part of the meetup. This could be any project large or small, whether that’s a complex production app or just something you threw together in a weekend. Drop us a line in the comments if you have a Meteor app you could show.\r\n\r\nSchedule:\r\n\r\n6:30pm - Doors open. Food, drinks, and mingling.\r\n7:00pm - Introduction to Meteor. Showcase of new tutorial and example apps.\r\n7:30pm - Deploy fest. Chance for everyone to install Meteor and deploy an example app.\r\n7:59pm - Short break. Take a group photo, tweet it. :)\r\n8:00pm - Q&A. Live Hangout with Meteor Core Dev.\r\n8:30 - Show & Tell. Built an app with Meteor before? We want to see it! Short, informal demos or talks from local developers.\r\n~9pm - Open coworking / socializing. Build something cool with what you’ve just learned.','<p>Come join Meteor Cape Town for Worldwide Meteor Day (meteorday.com)! The whole Meteor community is holding simultaneous meetups around the world on Nov 6, open to anyone who is interested in learning more about the Meteor platform. You’ll get to meet developers who have built things with Meteor here in Cape Town, play with the new Meteor examples and tutorial, and have Q&amp;A via Hangout with a core developer or expert from the community. We’ll have free Meteor t-shirts and stickers in the new design as well. Be sure to bring your laptops for the deploy fest and open coworking.</p>\n<p>If you’ve built a Meteor app before, we would love to see it during the show &amp; tell part of the meetup. This could be any project large or small, whether that’s a complex production app or just something you threw together in a weekend. Drop us a line in the comments if you have a Meteor app you could show.</p>\n<p>Schedule:</p>\n<p>6:30pm - Doors open. Food, drinks, and mingling.\n7:00pm - Introduction to Meteor. Showcase of new tutorial and example apps.\n7:30pm - Deploy fest. Chance for everyone to install Meteor and deploy an example app.\n7:59pm - Short break. Take a group photo, tweet it. :)\n8:00pm - Q&amp;A. Live Hangout with Meteor Core Dev.\n8:30 - Show &amp; Tell. Built an app with Meteor before? We want to see it! Short, informal demos or talks from local developers.\n~9pm - Open coworking / socializing. Build something cool with what you’ve just learned.</p>\n','2014-11-06','18:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','3 Ravenscraig Rd, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.9296553','18.443542699999966','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=3+Ravenscraig+Rd,+Woodstock,+Cape+Town,+7915,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc5d9c697d1ffd:0xc5007595d81ab65','http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-Cape-Town/events/213585632',50,'2015-02-13 07:00:37',1,'2015-10-20 10:04:34'),(24,1,'Exploring Modular Server-Side Rendering with React','exploring-modular-server-side-rendering-with-react','info@io.co.za','','React has significantly shifted the way we approach rendering for the browser. Two of the major benefits of the approach are the','React has significantly shifted the way we approach rendering for the browser. Two of the major benefits of the approach are the ability to encapsulate components fully in JavaScript and naturally render components on the server.\r\n\r\nGiven the above features, the modular question is how to install a single component or libraries of components? Approaches like Webpack are currently the primary means of tackling this, but handling this modularity across assets and with dual client and server rendering becomes the challenge here.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll describe and demonstrate an example rendering framework for React using jspm for managing modular react components on both the client and server and how it makes some of these problems easier.\r\n\r\nPresented by:\r\n\r\nGuy Paterson-Jones\r\nA pure-mathematician who usually enjoys tackling problems of topology, Guy unwittingly became the author of a rendering framework for React when he took an internship working with jspm over the Summer.\r\n\r\nGuy Bedford\r\nLiving the open source dream involving working large portions of his time for free while enjoying relative poverty, Guy is the creator of SystemJS and jspm.io, which tackle the problem of unifying multi-module-format dynamically-linked multi-version multi-package-registry modularity in the browser.','<p>React has significantly shifted the way we approach rendering for the browser. Two of the major benefits of the approach are the ability to encapsulate components fully in JavaScript and naturally render components on the server.</p>\n<p>Given the above features, the modular question is how to install a single component or libraries of components? Approaches like Webpack are currently the primary means of tackling this, but handling this modularity across assets and with dual client and server rendering becomes the challenge here.</p>\n<p>We\'ll describe and demonstrate an example rendering framework for React using jspm for managing modular react components on both the client and server and how it makes some of these problems easier.</p>\n<p>Presented by:</p>\n<p>Guy Paterson-Jones\nA pure-mathematician who usually enjoys tackling problems of topology, Guy unwittingly became the author of a rendering framework for React when he took an internship working with jspm over the Summer.</p>\n<p>Guy Bedford\nLiving the open source dream involving working large portions of his time for free while enjoying relative poverty, Guy is the creator of SystemJS and jspm.io, which tackle the problem of unifying multi-module-format dynamically-linked multi-version multi-package-registry modularity in the browser.</p>\n','2015-03-19','18:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','6 Beach Rd, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.9247137','18.448714600000017','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=6+Beach+Rd,+Woodstock,+Cape+Town,+7915,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc5d99ab8b510d:0x21d6043cd282127d','http://www.meetup.com/nodecpt/events/220703443',367,'2015-02-25 06:43:16',0,'2015-10-24 14:01:34'),(25,1,'March Meteor Meetup','march-meteor-meetup','info@nodeza.co.za','','Looking for a speaker / topic for next month. If one doesn\'t present itself, we will review the latest dev workshop and/or help ','Looking for a speaker / topic for next month. If one doesn\'t present itself, we will review the latest dev workshop and/or help people with their Meteor projects or questions.','<p>Looking for a speaker / topic for next month. If one doesn\'t present itself, we will review the latest dev workshop and/or help people with their Meteor projects or questions.</p>\n','2015-03-18','18:00:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','3 Ravenscraig Rd, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.9296553','18.443542699999966','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=3+Ravenscraig+Rd,+Woodstock,+Cape+Town,+7915,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc5d9c697d1ffd:0xc5007595d81ab65','http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-Cape-Town/events/220701645',88,'2015-03-13 07:36:27',0,'2015-10-20 10:03:53'),(26,1,'April Meteor Meetup','april-meteor-meetup','info@nodeza.co.za','','April Meteor Meetup','Our regular monthly meetup!','<p>Our regular monthly meetup!</p>\n','2015-04-15','20:00:00','23:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','3 Ravenscraig Rd, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.9296553','18.443542699999966','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=3+Ravenscraig+Rd,+Woodstock,+Cape+Town,+7915,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc5d9c697d1ffd:0xc5007595d81ab65','http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-Cape-Town/events/221820107/',170,'2015-04-14 08:10:54',1,'2015-10-20 10:04:04'),(28,1,'Redis and ReactJS for fast websites','redis-and-reactjs-for-fast-websites','info@nodeza.co.za','','We discuss the cost/benefit of Redis and React on Node for our use-case of digital media websites. ','We discuss the cost/benefit of Redis and React on Node for our use-case of digital media websites.\r\n\r\nRedis contains the entire database in memory. This limits the database size, but enables ultimate performance, i.e. fast websites.\r\n\r\nReact is an isomorphic library which can render HTML on the server, i.e. for fast \"pre-rendered\" web pages.\r\n\r\nWe present a Node Express example app, to store blog articles in a Redis database, and render them using React.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nAbout the speaker:\r\n\r\nEvan Summers has historically worked as a Java/enterprise developer. In 2014 he joined the IOL digital media team. This team built IOLmobile.co.za using Angular, Java and Node. More recently, they built MojoJazz.iol.co.za using ReactJS, Node and Redis.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nVenue kindly sponsored by IO check them out at [io.co.za](http://io.co.za)','<p>We discuss the cost/benefit of Redis and React on Node for our use-case of digital media websites.</p>\n<p>Redis contains the entire database in memory. This limits the database size, but enables ultimate performance, i.e. fast websites.</p>\n<p>React is an isomorphic library which can render HTML on the server, i.e. for fast &quot;pre-rendered&quot; web pages.</p>\n<p>We present a Node Express example app, to store blog articles in a Redis database, and render them using React.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>About the speaker:</p>\n<p>Evan Summers has historically worked as a Java/enterprise developer. In 2014 he joined the IOL digital media team. This team built IOLmobile.co.za using Angular, Java and Node. More recently, they built MojoJazz.iol.co.za using ReactJS, Node and Redis.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Venue kindly sponsored by IO check them out at <a href=\"http://io.co.za\">io.co.za</a></p>\n','2015-04-28','18:30:00','21:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','6 Beach Rd, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.9247137','18.448714600000017','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=6+Beach+Rd,+Woodstock,+Cape+Town,+7915,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc5d99ab8b510d:0x21d6043cd282127d','http://www.meetup.com/nodecpt/events/221949817/',1160,'2015-04-20 10:38:56',0,'2015-10-22 04:02:06'),(29,1,'ReactJS for fast websites: Part 2','reactjs-for-fast-websites-part-2','info@nodeza.co.za','','Following on the last talk by Evan Summers we present the second part focussing on the React side of the story.','Following on the last talk by Evan Summers (http://nodeza.co.za/events/redis-and-reactjs-for-fast-websites) we present the second part focussing on the React side of the story.\r\n\r\nReact is an isomorphic library which can render HTML on the server.\r\n\r\nWe discuss the cost/benefit of React on Node for our use-case of digital media websites, e.g. for search and social bots, and also pre-rendering cachable pages for a faster user experience.\r\n\r\nWe continue our Node Express example app from last time, where we stored blog articles in a Redis database. We now render them using React on Node. ','<p>Following on the last talk by Evan Summers (http://nodeza.co.za/events/redis-and-reactjs-for-fast-websites) we present the second part focussing on the React side of the story.</p>\n<p>React is an isomorphic library which can render HTML on the server.</p>\n<p>We discuss the cost/benefit of React on Node for our use-case of digital media websites, e.g. for search and social bots, and also pre-rendering cachable pages for a faster user experience.</p>\n<p>We continue our Node Express example app from last time, where we stored blog articles in a Redis database. We now render them using React on Node.</p>\n','2015-05-19','18:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','6 Beach Rd, Mouille Point, Cape Town, 8005, South Africa','-33.9247137','18.4487146','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=6+Beach+Rd,+Mouille+Point,+Cape+Town,+8005,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc67343dd19199:0x6b82684ba013bcfc','http://www.meetup.com/nodecpt/events/222217411/',101,'2015-05-14 14:40:32',1,'2015-10-25 23:43:25'),(30,1,'Meteorites, assemble','meteorites-assemble','info@nodeza.co.za','','Meteor JHB is back and we have some exciting things to present.','Meteor JHB is back and we have some exciting things to present.\r\n\r\nWe do have to pay to use this venue so we\'ll be asking everyone attending to contribute R50. Drinks will be for your own account.\r\n\r\nSeats limited to 20 people so RSVP fast!\r\n\r\nAGENDA\r\n\r\n• New Compose MongoDB+ deployment types - Kyle McLaren\r\n\r\n• Using Bower packages in your Meteor app - Kyle McLaren\r\n\r\n• Demo - Paul Sainsbury\r\n\r\n• Demo - John Scarborough ','<p>Meteor JHB is back and we have some exciting things to present.</p>\n<p>We do have to pay to use this venue so we\'ll be asking everyone attending to contribute R50. Drinks will be for your own account.</p>\n<p>Seats limited to 20 people so RSVP fast!</p>\n<p>AGENDA</p>\n<p>• New Compose MongoDB+ deployment types - Kyle McLaren</p>\n<p>• Using Bower packages in your Meteor app - Kyle McLaren</p>\n<p>• Demo - Paul Sainsbury</p>\n<p>• Demo - John Scarborough</p>\n','2015-07-22','19:00:00','00:00:00','Gauteng','Randburg','','40 Peter St, Randburg, 2194, South Africa','-26.0842431','27.98012940000001','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=40+Peter+St,+Randburg,+2194,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1e9574f85636002f:0x51d063bbef2094f7','http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-Johannesburg/events/223831192',0,'2015-10-22 09:43:14',0,'2015-10-22 09:43:14'),(31,1,'Meteor Shower','meteor-shower','info@nodeza.co.za','','Two events in one year? Yup! You\'re not seeing things, we\'re having another meet up. It\'s a veritable meteor shower of events. :','Two events in one year? Yup! You\'re not seeing things, we\'re having another meet up. It\'s a veritable meteor shower of events. :-)\r\n\r\nWe will have some topics prepared, but would love some talks from the group. If you have any code you\'ve been working on, side projects, real life problems, or questions - we\'d love to hear from you.','<p>Two events in one year? Yup! You\'re not seeing things, we\'re having another meet up. It\'s a veritable meteor shower of events. :-)</p>\n<p>We will have some topics prepared, but would love some talks from the group. If you have any code you\'ve been working on, side projects, real life problems, or questions - we\'d love to hear from you.</p>\n','2015-09-22','18:30:00','00:00:00','Gauteng','Sandton','','102 Western Service Rd, Sandton, 2148, South Africa','-26.0685398','28.08953870000005','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=102+Western+Service+Rd,+Sandton,+2148,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1e95728d4f3b4c23:0x19060af6374a53f5','http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-Johannesburg/events/224700292/',23,'2015-10-22 09:47:07',0,'2015-10-26 13:20:43'),(32,1,'Getting Started with Meteor - Building a chat application (Slack style)','getting-started-with-meteor-building-a-chat-application-slack-style','info@nodeza.co.za','','Lance Haig will share his experience in getting started with Meteor and take us through Tim Brandin\'s slides on building a chat ','Lance Haig will share his experience in getting started with Meteor and take us through Tim Brandin\'s slides on building a chat application a la Slack. If you\'re a salted Meteor developer, come and add your two cents to help fast track the newbies.','<p>Lance Haig will share his experience in getting started with Meteor and take us through Tim Brandin\'s slides on building a chat application a la Slack. If you\'re a salted Meteor developer, come and add your two cents to help fast track the newbies.</p>\n','2015-07-15','18:00:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','3 Ravenscraig Rd, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.9296553','18.443542699999966','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=3+Ravenscraig+Rd,+Woodstock,+Cape+Town,+7915,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc5d9c697d1ffd:0xc5007595d81ab65','http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-Cape-Town/events/223329392/',0,'2015-10-22 09:51:28',0,'2015-10-22 09:51:28'),(33,1,'Meteor and ES6 + Devshop Vids','meteor-and-es6-devshop-vids','info@nodeza.co.za','','We need to find a new venue before next week, or the meetup will be cancelled, anyone with a suggestion please comment on the me','We need to find a new venue before next week, or the meetup will be cancelled, anyone with a suggestion please comment on the meetup page.\r\n\r\nIf no topic/speaker pops up before the meeting, we\'ll be watching some of the community videos with discussion afterwards. Please bring your meteor projects along if you are comfortable to give a demo (HDMI and Apple TV available).','<p>We need to find a new venue before next week, or the meetup will be cancelled, anyone with a suggestion please comment on the meetup page.</p>\n<p>If no topic/speaker pops up before the meeting, we\'ll be watching some of the community videos with discussion afterwards. Please bring your meteor projects along if you are comfortable to give a demo (HDMI and Apple TV available).</p>\n','2015-08-19','18:00:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','Old Castle Brewery, Beach Rd, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.9248885','18.44773609999993','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=Old+Castle+Brewery&ftid=0x1dcc5d99a8bcd1cb:0x76681ae213743dc1','http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-Cape-Town/events/223768711/',2,'2015-10-22 09:55:20',0,'2015-10-25 02:52:19'),(34,1,'Meteor Worldwide Hackathon 2015','meteor-worldwide-hackathon-2015','info@nodeza.co.za','','Calling all meteorites! Please join us for the Meteor Worldwide Distributed Hackathon 2015.','Calling all meteorites!\r\n\r\nPlease join us for the Meteor Worldwide Distributed Hackathon 2015. We will be building something awesome in a 24 hour period over the weekend of 10-11 Oct.\r\n\r\nIf you are still a meteor newbie, but can help us with the artwork or copy writing or video making, don\'t discount your contribution, we NEED you.\r\n\r\nPlease join our meteor-cape-town slack team here:\r\n\r\nhttps://slackinmeteorct.herokuapp.com/\r\n\r\nPlease post your app ideas in the #hackathon2015 channel so we can put it to a vote in the next couple of days. We are allowed to build some packages in advance, provided that hey are shared with the community and useful outside of our app.','<p>Calling all meteorites!</p>\n<p>Please join us for the Meteor Worldwide Distributed Hackathon 2015. We will be building something awesome in a 24 hour period over the weekend of 10-11 Oct.</p>\n<p>If you are still a meteor newbie, but can help us with the artwork or copy writing or video making, don\'t discount your contribution, we NEED you.</p>\n<p>Please join our meteor-cape-town slack team here:</p>\n<p>https://slackinmeteorct.herokuapp.com/</p>\n<p>Please post your app ideas in the #hackathon2015 channel so we can put it to a vote in the next couple of days. We are allowed to build some packages in advance, provided that hey are shared with the community and useful outside of our app.</p>\n','2015-10-10','13:00:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','Old Castle Brewery, Beach Rd, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.9248885','18.44773609999993','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=Old+Castle+Brewery&ftid=0x1dcc5d99a8bcd1cb:0x76681ae213743dc1','http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-Cape-Town/events/225416539/',23,'2015-10-22 09:57:52',0,'2015-10-26 13:20:43'),(35,1,'How was the global hackathon?','how-was-the-global-hackathon','info@nodeza.co.za','','We\'ll reminisce about the Meteor Global Distributed Hackathon a bit and share what we\'ve learnt. ','We\'ll reminisce about the Meteor Global Distributed Hackathon a bit and share what we\'ve learnt. \r\n\r\nIf you\'ve created something with meteor lately, Please bring your project along and share your triumphs and frustrations in a lightning talk (Chromecast available).','<p>We\'ll reminisce about the Meteor Global Distributed Hackathon a bit and share what we\'ve learnt.</p>\n<p>If you\'ve created something with meteor lately, Please bring your project along and share your triumphs and frustrations in a lightning talk (Chromecast available).</p>\n','2015-10-21','18:00:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','7 Ravenscraig Rd, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.9300696','18.443137999999976','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=7+Ravenscraig+Rd,+Woodstock,+Cape+Town,+7915,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc5d9c68f779dd:0x3d21b5b548c2290c','http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-Cape-Town/events/223768757/',26,'2015-10-22 10:00:09',0,'2015-10-26 13:20:43'),(36,1,'International Nodebots Day 2015 in Cape Town','international-nodebots-day-2015-in-cape-town','info@nodeza.co.za','','Join us for International Nodebots Day 2015 and hack hardware using Javascript.','Join us for International Nodebots Day 2015 and hack hardware using Javascript.\r\n\r\nLet\'s decouple Javascript from the DOM and built obstacle avoiding and line following Javascript robots instead.\r\n\r\nEntry fee: R150\r\n\r\nWhat will be provided on the day\r\n\r\n• Hardware and instructions for building Nodebots - obstacle avoiding or line following\r\n\r\n• Food\r\n\r\n• Arduinos and Tessels (tessel.io) to experiment with\r\n\r\n• Electronic components\r\n\r\nWhat to bring\r\n\r\n• A laptop if you have one\r\n\r\n• An Arduino starter kit if you have one\r\n\r\n• A PS3 dual shock if you have one laying around\r\n\r\n• A soldering iron and other tools\r\n\r\n• A 9V battery\r\n\r\n• One packet of decent 4xAA batteries\r\n\r\n• Feel free to bring your own project you would like to work on the day\r\n\r\nSee more here:\r\n\r\nhttp://node-ardx.org/\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rwaldron/johnny-five','<p>Join us for International Nodebots Day 2015 and hack hardware using Javascript.</p>\n<p>Let\'s decouple Javascript from the DOM and built obstacle avoiding and line following Javascript robots instead.</p>\n<p>Entry fee: R150</p>\n<p>What will be provided on the day</p>\n<p>• Hardware and instructions for building Nodebots - obstacle avoiding or line following</p>\n<p>• Food</p>\n<p>• Arduinos and Tessels (tessel.io) to experiment with</p>\n<p>• Electronic components</p>\n<p>What to bring</p>\n<p>• A laptop if you have one</p>\n<p>• An Arduino starter kit if you have one</p>\n<p>• A PS3 dual shock if you have one laying around</p>\n<p>• A soldering iron and other tools</p>\n<p>• A 9V battery</p>\n<p>• One packet of decent 4xAA batteries</p>\n<p>• Feel free to bring your own project you would like to work on the day</p>\n<p>See more here:</p>\n<p>http://node-ardx.org/</p>\n<p>https://github.com/rwaldron/johnny-five</p>\n','2015-07-25','09:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','17 Dock Rd, V & A Waterfront, Cape Town, 8001, South Africa','-33.904324','18.41814439999996','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=17+Dock+Rd,+V+%26+A+Waterfront,+Cape+Town,+8001,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc675066bddc05:0x34afeb8fb4541af8','http://www.meetup.com/Cape-Town-Nodebots/events/223635419/',0,'2015-10-22 10:07:19',0,'2015-10-22 10:07:19');
